<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 13 at 9:46AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...Patchy Dense Fog Lingering Across Southern Hidalgo County...
Surface observations and satellite imagery indicate that areas of
locally dense fog are persisting across southwestern and south
central Hidalgo County. Visibilities will generally be reduced to
around 1 mile or less in the fog, with more dense fog reducing
the visibility to around one quarter of a mile in the McAllen
area.
These areas of fog will steadily dissipate by Midday.
Motorists in southwestern and south central Hidalgo County are
urged to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and avoid
following other cars too closely in any fog through Noontime.</description>
